  "text": "We also report an important and previously unidentified role of the DNA repair protein Ku80 in suppressing S. pneumoniaeinduced genotoxicity. This observation is consistent with the known role of Ku80 in protecting alveolar epithelial cells (and other cell types) from gamma-irradiation-induced DSBs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Overall, our data suggest a genotoxic model of pneumococcal pathogenesis whereby pneumococcal spxB-derived H 2 O 2 induces host DNA damage that overwhelms the Ku80-dependent NHEJ repair pathway, leading to cell death. Ultimately, via increased DNA damage, the resultant cell death and tissue damage could enable pneumococci to become more virulent and invasive.",
